                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-255-off1431 t18291029-255-crimeloc1434"></join>. At ten o'clock on the evening of the 30th of October I was in my back parlour, and saw the prisoner come into my shop - I had seen him before, but not in my shop; he snatched up a pair of scales, and ran off - I followed, and caught him a few yards from the door; he dropped the scales - I know them to be mine: he ran very well, and spoke like a sober man - these are the scales.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was intoxicated - I had drank a great deal of liquor; if I had been sober I should not have done it.</p>
